13/01/2006
ZAGREB, Croatia -- Prime Minister Ivo Sanader is proposing all past and future testimonies by President Stipe Mesic before The Hague-based war crimes tribunal be declassified. The two officials discussed the idea on Thursday (12 January), with Mesic reportedly agreeing that the move would provide maximum transparency in all cases regarding Croatian indictees. (Novi List - 13/01/06; HINA - 12/01/06)
